5000|$|On many cars, the {{accelerator}} pedal motion is communicated via the throttle cable, {{to activate the}} throttle linkages, which move the throttle plate. In cars with electronic <b>throttle</b> <b>control</b> (also known as [...] "drive-by-wire"), an electric motor <b>controls</b> the <b>throttle</b> linkages and {{the accelerator}} pedal connects not to the throttle body, but to a sensor, which sends the pedal position to the Engine <b>Control</b> <b>Unit</b> (ECU). The ECU determines the throttle opening based on accelerator pedal position and inputs from other engine sensors.|$|R
