50|$|The {{helicopter}} {{is controlled}} using a two lever <b>control</b> <b>unit.</b> The <b>controls</b> operate {{similar to a}} real helicopter. The <b>throttle</b> <b>control</b> provides proportional control of the blade speed. The pitch control provides for tilting the Vertibird forward or backward. During flight the VertiBird {{is subject to the}} same physical flight characteristics as a real helicopter. This included ground-effects for low level hovering, plus altitude gains and losses when changing direction. Overall the VertiBird is easy to learn how to pilot for basic flight, but precision flying will require some patience and time on the controls as in a real helicopter.|$|R
